Module bundlers like webpackl are tools used in modern web development to manage and 
bundle various modules and assets within a web application.

They allow devs to organise and optimise code.

Web packs enable the use of modular programming in javascript where code is organised into seperate modules.
Each handling it's own specific functionality.

They also manage dependencies between modules, ensuring that correct loading is maintained.

The provide the option to plugins to extend functionality of module bundlers.

They provide a development server.

When you use React, Web pack is included as part of the build set up.